-> All are object oriented languages.
-> Scala and Ruby are pure oo languages. Everything in these languages is instance of a class.
-> In java primitives are outside of OO model.
-> In Scala and Ruby, all operations on entites are via method calls.
-> 1.hashCode and 1.toString are legal in Scala.

Traits, Interfaces and Mixins

-> Scala has traits.
-> Java has interfaces.
-> Ruby has mixins.
